$ Oracle: Init parameter PGA_AGGREGATE_TARGET
@ pga_aggregate_target

If the value `pga_aggregate_target` is not set to 0, Oracle sets it to the greater value of 20% of the size of the SGA or 10 MB.
-
If the value is nonzero, the value of `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/workarea_size_policy` is automatically set to `auto`.

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/pga_aggregate/limit`

  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/memory-management

  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters
